main event: An aircraft commander reported a sighting of a round, blue-white colored object in the Pacific Ocean on 9 May 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes before it suddenly disappeared and later resurfaced., The pilot estimated the object to be 15-20 miles in front of the aircraft at approximately 10,000 ft., The object had rapid speed and performed fast maneuvers with a change of direction., The weather conditions were clear with no cloud cover., The conclusion of the report suggested it could be a satellite.
